snippet.textDisplay:
In USA, the “all natural spring water, bottled at its source” is tap water, bottled from the tap. They might throw a rusty metal spring in there to back up their use of the description “spring water”. I buy the store brand. It’s cheap, and convenient. Or I will bring a water bottle from home with filtered tap water in it. Funny how we now bring water with us everywhere we go - but in my defense, I live in California, which is a desert. It’s dry here, and I get thirsty.

My home’s tap water unfiltered has a certain phlegmy quality to it. I will drink it in small amounts when swallowing pills, but doesn’t taste the same as my fridge’s filtered water. (which I have to replace the filter every couple months).

If drinking tap water sounds gross, where do you think the water source for soda comes from?
